	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The struggle is that most of the NES games uses tiny &quot;general&quot; tiles to compose the background, so they could use them over and over again (with a different palette), and I think that's almost a form of art (like on the first level of Castlevania the base of the columns inside are as good to be the shape of the fountain outside and it looks great). But my backgrounds look like exactly what they are, and I think they aren't as great.<br /><br />BTW Frankengraphics what did you &quot;expect&quot;? Do you mean the triangular pediment or the simplicity of the roofs?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


